Here's a C# code snippet that demonstrates how to create custom dimensions for holes in a plate using the Advance Steel .NET API. This code assumes that you have a plate object and that you want to dimension all the holes in it.

Please note that you may need to adjust the code to fit your specific requirements and project setup.

```csharp
using Autodesk.AdvanceSteel.Geometry;
using Autodesk.AdvanceSteel.Modelling;
using Autodesk.AdvanceSteel.DocumentManager;

public void DimensionHolesInPlate(Plate plate)
{
    // Get the bottom-left corner of the plate as the reference point (0, 0)
    Point3d refPoint = plate.InsertionPoint;
    double plateWidth = plate.Width;
    double plateLength = plate.Length;
    refPoint.X -= plateWidth / 2;
    refPoint.Y -= plateLength / 2;

    // Get all the holes in the plate
    List<Hole> holes = new List<Hole>();
    foreach (var item in plate.Items)
    {
        if (item is Hole)
        {
            holes.Add((Hole)item);
        }
    }

    // Create a new drawing document
    DrawingDocument drawingDoc = DrawingDocument.Create();

    // Add the plate to the drawing
    drawingDoc.ActiveSheet.AddItem(plate);

    // Create custom dimensions for each hole
    foreach (Hole hole in holes)
    {
        // Calculate the position of the hole relative to the reference point
        Point3d holePoint = hole.InsertionPoint;
        holePoint.X -= refPoint.X;
        holePoint.Y -= refPoint.Y;

        // Create a new linear dimension for the X-coordinate
        LinearDimension xDim = LinearDimension.Create(holePoint, new Vector3d(1, 0, 0));
        xDim.Text = $"{holePoint.X:F2}";
        xDim.DimensionLinePosition = DimensionLinePositionType.DimLineAbove;
        xDim.ExtensionLineLength = 5;
        drawingDoc.ActiveSheet.AddItem(xDim);

        // Create a new linear dimension for the Y-coordinate
        LinearDimension yDim = LinearDimension.Create(holePoint, new Vector3d(0, 1, 0));
        yDim.Text = $"{holePoint.Y:F2}";
        yDim.DimensionLinePosition = DimensionLinePositionType.DimLineRight;
        yDim.ExtensionLineLength = 5;
        drawingDoc.ActiveSheet.AddItem(yDim);
    }

    // Save and close the drawing document
    drawingDoc.SaveAs(@"C:\temp\HoleDimensions.dst");
    drawingDoc.Close();
}
```

This code creates a new drawing document, adds the plate to the drawing, and then iterates through all the holes in the plate. For each hole, it calculates the position of the hole relative to the bottom-left corner of the plate and then creates two linear dimensions for the X and Y coordinates. The dimensions are then added to the drawing, and the drawing is saved and closed.

